 You MUST create a task for each of these items and complete them in order:
 
 1. **Explore project context** — check files, docs, recent commits
-2. **Offer visual companion** (if topic will involve visual questions) — this is its own message, not combined with a clarifying question. See the Visual Companion section below.
-3. **Ask clarifying questions** — one at a time, understand purpose/constraints/success criteria
-4. **Propose 2-3 approaches** — with trade-offs and your recommendation
-5. **Present design** — in sections scaled to their complexity, get user approval after each section
-6. **Write design doc** — save to `docs/superpowers/specs/YYYY-MM-DD-<topic>-design.md` and commit
-7. **Spec review loop** — dispatch spec-document-reviewer subagent with precisely crafted review context (never your session history); fix issues and re-dispatch until approved (max 3 iterations, then surface to human)
-8. **User reviews written spec** — ask user to review the spec file before proceeding
-9. **Transition to implementation** — invoke writing-plans skill to create implementation plan
+2. **Check memory for prior context** — ask the user: "Want me to check memory for prior context on this?" If yes, run `/recall` with the topic. Do not auto-recall — past decisions may bias exploration.
+3. **Offer visual companion** (if topic will involve visual questions) — this is its own message, not combined with a clarifying question. See the Visual Companion section below.
+4. **Ask clarifying questions** — one at a time, understand purpose/constraints/success criteria
+5. **Propose 2-3 approaches** — with trade-offs and your recommendation
+6. **Present design** — in sections scaled to their complexity, get user approval after each section
+7. **Write design doc** — save to `docs/superpowers/specs/YYYY-MM-DD-<topic>-design.md`
+8. **Spec review loop** — dispatch spec-document-reviewer subagent with precisely crafted review context (never your session history); fix issues and re-dispatch until approved (max 3 iterations, then surface to human)
+9. **User reviews written spec** — ask user to review the spec file before proceeding
+10. **Choose execution strategy** — ask the user which implementation approach to use:
+    - **Sequential** (default): invoke writing-plans → executing-plans (single agent, step by step)
+    - **Parallel subagents**: invoke writing-plans → subagent-driven-development (independent tasks in parallel, no inter-agent communication)
+    - **Agent teams**: invoke writing-plans, then spawn a coordinated team via `/team-feature` (persistent agents with tmux panes, shared task list, inter-agent messaging — best for large features with cross-cutting concerns)
+11. **Agent type assignments** (skip for sequential) — present an agent assignment table for each planned task. Analyze the design to suggest the best agent type per task based on language/domain. Present as a multi-select table for the user to review and override:
+
+    ```
+    Task                          | Suggested Agent                          | Override?
+    ------------------------------|------------------------------------------|----------
+    Implement auth middleware      | systems-programming:rust-pro             | [ ]
+    Add API endpoints              | systems-programming:golang-pro           | [ ]
+    Write Solidity contracts       | blockchain-web3:blockchain-developer     | [ ]
+    Update Nix config              | general-purpose                          | [ ]
+    ...                            | ...                                      | [ ]
+    ```
+
+    **Agent type selection guide:**
+
+    | Domain / Language      | Agent Type                               |
+    |------------------------|------------------------------------------|
+    | Rust                   | systems-programming:rust-pro             |
+    | Go                     | systems-programming:golang-pro           |
+    | C                      | systems-programming:c-pro                |
+    | C++                    | systems-programming:cpp-pro              |
+    | Solidity / Web3 / DeFi | blockchain-web3:blockchain-developer     |
+    | Security audit         | security-scanning:security-auditor       |
+    | Code review            | git-pr-workflows:code-reviewer           |
+    | General / other        | general-purpose (default)                |
+
+    Ask the user: "Here are my suggested agent assignments. Change any you'd like, or approve to continue." The user can override any row. Save the final assignments into the spec under an `## Agent Assignments` section so writing-plans and execution skills can reference them.
+12. **Transition to implementation** — invoke writing-plans skill to create the plan (include agent assignments), then execute with the chosen strategy
 
